description: Jiefang Village is a part of Yongsan 2 Street, Yongsan District, Seoul, South Korea. It is a village formed on the hillside under the Namsan Mountain. At the time of liberation in 1945, people who returned from overseas, those who came to Korea from the north, and those who took refuge due to the Korean War settled in Korea, so it was called Liberation Village.
